+# MJX XML Generation
+
+MJX model assets live in:
+
+```text
+puppersimMJX/assets
+```
+
+The committed assets should already be enough for training and playback. Use these commands only when regenerating XML, camera variants, or AprilTag room assets.
+
+Run commands from the repository root.
+
+## Fix URDF
+
+Adds MuJoCo metadata and relative mesh paths to the source URDF:
+
+```bash
+python puppersimMJX/xml_generation/fix_urdf.py \
+  --urdf_path puppersimMJX/assets/pupper_v2a.urdf \
+  --output_path puppersimMJX/assets/pupper_v2a.fixed.urdf \
+  --meshdir meshes
+```
+
+## Create Stable MJX XML
+
+Builds the stable MJX XML used by locomotion tasks:
+
+```bash
+python puppersimMJX/xml_generation/create_mujoco_xml.py \
+  --input puppersimMJX/assets/pupper_v2a.fixed.xml \
+  --output puppersimMJX/assets/pupper_v2_final_stable.xml \
+  --force
+```
+
+## Add Front Camera
+
+Creates the camera-enabled XML used by camera-style navigation tasks:
+
+```bash
+python puppersimMJX/xml_generation/add_camera_to_xml.py \
+  --xml-path puppersimMJX/assets/pupper_v2_final_stable.xml \
+  --output puppersimMJX/assets/pupper_v2_final_stable_cam.xml \
+  --force
+```
+
+## Create AprilTag Room Assets
+
+Generates AprilTag textures, the tag quad mesh, and an AprilTag room XML:
+
+```bash
+python puppersimMJX/xml_generation/create_apriltag_room_assets.py \
+  --input-xml puppersimMJX/assets/pupper_v2_final_stable_cam.xml \
+  --output-xml puppersimMJX/assets/pupper_v2_apriltag_room.xml \
+  --textures-dir puppersimMJX/assets/textures \
+  --meshes-dir puppersimMJX/assets/meshes
+```
+
+For a larger single good tag and no bad tag:
+
+```bash
+python puppersimMJX/xml_generation/create_apriltag_room_assets.py \
+  --tag-half 0.30 \
+  --no-include-bad-tag
+```
+
+## Path Rule
+
+Keep asset references relative. XML files should use paths such as:
+
+```xml
+<compiler meshdir="meshes/" />
+<mesh file="Cube.003.obj" />
+<texture file="textures/apriltag_36h11_id101.png" />
+```
+
+Do not commit machine-specific absolute paths like `/home/...` inside XML or URDF assets.
